Team-1 | in-progress | Explorer — Website Redesign

# STORY MAP
# Stories define the user-facing value. Tasks inside each phase deliver the story.

Story-1 | todo | Recipient converts to sender
	# Acceptance: A person who received a token can land on sgraph.ai,
	# understand what the product does in < 90s, and find a CTA to try it.
	# Design success: "Already have a token? →" in header. Hero shows gallery.
	# Tracking: Phase 2 (homepage) + Phase 3 (nav)

Story-2 | todo | Evaluator trusts the security
	# Acceptance: A CISO-level evaluator can find /security/, read architecture
	# explanation, see the 3 subpoena/breach/retention Q&As, and leave satisfied.
	# Design success: 6-sentence policy visible. GDPR-by-architecture explicit.
	# Tracking: Phase 1 (new pages)

Story-3 | todo | Visitor discovers v0.3.0 features
	# Acceptance: A new visitor can see gallery, folder browser, SgPrint
	# demonstrated with real screenshots — on the homepage and /features/.
	# Design success: No more "zero product screenshots". Every claim has a visual.
	# Tracking: Phase 1 (/features/) + Phase 2 (homepage feature showcase)

Story-4 | todo | Every claim is verifiable
	# Acceptance: Every competitive or security claim on sgraph.ai links to
	# qa.send.sgraph.ai as the proof layer. No unsubstantiated claims.
	# Design success: "See it tested →" links on /features/. Verify zero cookies
	# in DevTools instruction on /security/.
	# Tracking: Phase 1 (claim review tasks) + QA gate

Story-5 | todo | PR 1 shipped — all new content, zero deletions
	# Acceptance: PR 1 is merged, deployed, and all new pages return 200.
	# No old pages removed. CI smoke tests pass.
	# Design success: Villager team can begin their gate (Team 3 unblocked).
	# Tracking: Phase 7 (CI) + Definition of Done

